# Web Frontend (Next.js on Vercel)

## REQUIRED design skills (read & follow before building any UI)
When designing, building, refactoring, or reviewing ANY web UI in `apps/web/**`, you MUST
read and follow these skills first:
- `ui-ux-pro-max` — design system, color/typography/layout selection, accessibility & UX quality gates.
- `design-taste-frontend` — high-agency premium frontend execution (anti-slop, motion, materiality).

Treat them as mandatory pre-work, not optional references. Run the `ui-ux-pro-max` design-system
step before implementing new pages.

## Conventions
- Functional components only. No classes. No default exports for components.
- Tailwind CSS. Share a single design-tokens file with mobile where practical.
- All Turkish UI strings via i18next (no hardcoded copy in components).
- Heatmap = `react-leaflet` + `leaflet.heat`. Map weight = sum of per-class severities at a point.
- PDF export ("Şikayet Dosyası İndir") uses `@react-pdf/renderer` in a Client Component (`"use client"`).
- CSV export via `papaparse`.
- Talk to the Go API only through a Next.js route handler proxy (`/api/score`), never expose backend keys client-side.
- Provide loading (skeleton), empty, and error states for every async view.
